# JavaScript Function Basics

```javascript
// Function declaration
function greet(name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

// Function call
const message = greet('World');
console.log(message);
```

## Flowchart of Execution

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Start] --> B{Call Function}
    B -->|Yes| C[Execute Function]
    C --> D[Return Value]
    D --> E[Use Value]
    E --> F[End]
```

## Function Parameters and Return

```javascript
// Function with parameters
function add(a, b) {
    return a + b;
}

// Using the function
const sum = add(5, 3);
console.log(`Sum: ${sum}`);
```

### Comparison Table

| Feature | Parameter | Return Value |
|---------|-----------|--------------|
| Purpose | Input values | Output result |
| Example | `a, b` | `a + b` |

# JavaScript Function Expressions

```javascript
// Function expression
const multiply = function(x, y) {
    return x * y;
};

// Function call
const product = multiply(4, 5);
console.log(`Product: ${product}`);
```

